Class Statistics

  • java.lang.Object
    • AbstractObservation
      • Observation
        • Statistics
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DateTimeComparable
    public class Statistics
extends Observation
implements DateTimeComparable
    Statistics class that extends the Observation class and implements the DateTimeComparable interface. Holds a special type of Observation that has, in addition to a value and stid, variables holding the date, the number of valid stations in the statistic, and the StatsType of the statistic.
    Version:
    2018-10-03 Lab 14
    Author:
    Julia Davies

                  java.lang.String stid,
                  java.lang.String dateTimeStr,
                  int numberOfValidStations,
                  StatsType inStatType)
        A Statistics constructor that sets the values given as parameters
        Parameters:
        value - the double value of the statistic
        stid - the string stid of the statistic
        dateTimeStr - A string that should follow the format of DATE_TIME_FORMAT
        numberOfValidStations - the int number of valid stations used in calculating the statistic
        inStatType - a StatsType, either MAXIMUM, MINIMUM, TOTAL, or AVERAGE.
